---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Resources" description="Books, documentaries, primary sources, and organizations for those who want to go deeper — curated for accuracy and accessibility, not ideology.">

  <section class="hero" style="padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1 style="font-size: var(--text-5xl);">Resources</h1>
      <p class="subhead">For those who want to go deeper. Books, documentaries, primary sources, and organizations — curated for accuracy and accessibility.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:42rem;margin:0 auto;">

      <h2>Essential Books</h2>
      <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">The Ethnic Cleansing of Palestine</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Ilan Pappé (2006) — Oneworld Publications</p>
          <p>A detailed account of Plan Dalet and the systematic expulsion of Palestinians in 1948, based on Israeli military archives and oral histories.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">The Birth of the Palestinian Refugee Problem, 1947–1949</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Benny Morris (1988) — Cambridge University Press</p>
          <p>The foundational scholarly work on the Palestinian refugee crisis, written by an Israeli historian using declassified Israeli state archives. Revisited edition published in 2004.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">The Iron Wall: Israel and the Arab World</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Avi Shlaim (2001) — W.W. Norton</p>
          <p>A comprehensive history of Israel's relationship with the Arab world, written by an Israeli-British historian and one of the "New Historians."</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">The Question of Palestine</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Edward Said (1979) — Vintage Books</p>
          <p>A foundational work by the Palestinian-American scholar, examining the Palestinian experience through the lens of postcolonial studies and international law.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>Documentaries &amp; Films</h2>
      <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">Al-Nakba: The Palestinian Catastrophe</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Al Jazeera (2008) — 4-part documentary series</p>
          <p>A comprehensive documentary tracing the history of Palestine from 1799 to 1948, featuring interviews with historians, survivors, and archival footage.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">1948: Creation & Catastrophe</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Ahlam Muhtaseb & Andy Trimlett (2017)</p>
          <p>Told through the voices of both Palestinians and Israelis, this documentary provides a balanced account of the events of 1948.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">The Gatekeepers</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Dror Moreh (2012)</p>
          <p>Interviews with all six surviving former heads of Shin Bet, Israel's internal security service, who speak candidly about the occupation and its consequences.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>Primary Sources</h2>
      <ul style="margin-bottom:var(--space-xl);padding-left:var(--space-xl);">
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>UN General Assembly Resolution 181</strong> (Nov 29, 1947) — The Partition Plan</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>UN General Assembly Resolution 194</strong> (Dec 11, 1948) — Right of Return</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>UN Security Council Resolution 242</strong> (Nov 22, 1967) — "Land for Peace" framework</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>The Balfour Declaration</strong> (Nov 2, 1917) — Full text</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>Israeli Declaration of Independence</strong> (May 14, 1948)</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>ICJ Advisory Opinion</strong> (July 19, 2024) — Legality of the Israeli Occupation</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);"><strong>Amnesty International Report</strong> (Feb 2022) — "Israel's Apartheid Against Palestinians"</li>
        <li><strong>Human Rights Watch Report</strong> (April 2021) — "A Threshold Crossed"</li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h2>Organizations</h2>
      <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">B'Tselem</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">The Israeli Information Center for Human Rights in the Occupied Territories</p>
          <p>Israel's leading human rights organization, documenting human rights violations in the occupied territories since 1989.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">Institute for Palestine Studies</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">Established 1963, Beirut</p>
          <p>The oldest independent research institute devoted to the study of Palestine, publishing the Journal of Palestine Studies since 1971.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);">
          <h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);">UNRWA</h3>
          <p style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0;color:var(--flint);">United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees</p>
          <p>Established in 1949 to provide relief to Palestinian refugees. Still operating today, serving more than 5.9 million registered refugees.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
      <p>All statistics on this site draw from the following primary and secondary sources, cited inline:</p>
      <ul style="margin-bottom:var(--space-lg);padding-left:var(--space-xl);">
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);">British Mandate Government census data (1922, 1931)</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);">Anglo-American Committee of Inquiry (1946)</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);">UNSCOP Report (1947)</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);">UNRWA registration statistics (annual, 1950–present)</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom:var(--space-sm);">Israeli Central Bureau of Statistics</li>
        <li>Peer-reviewed academic publications (cited by author and title)</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
